# Tehila Bodyshop CRM – Cursor rules

## Stack
- Next.js 14+ App Router, TypeScript, Supabase (Postgres, Auth Email+Password, Storage), TailwindCSS

## Database
- All writes must respect RLS. Do not bypass RLS.
- Every workflow/status transition must insert an `audit_events` row (entity_type, entity_id, action, user_id, payload).
- Workflow state lives in `case_workflow_steps`; do not jump steps or skip validation.

## Blocking rules (enforce in app + optionally in DB)
- ENTER_WORK: only when `cases.parts_status = 'AVAILABLE'`.
- READY_FOR_OFFICE / CLOSE_CASE: block if any `bodywork_extras.status = 'IN_TREATMENT'` or required CEO approvals missing/rejected.
- FIXCAR_PHOTOS: cannot complete without `cases.fixcar_link`.
- WHEELS_CHECK: auto-skip when vehicle age <= 2 years.

## Roles & access
- Branch-scoped access: filter by `profiles.branch_id` for current user.
- SERVICE_MANAGER: workflow control. OFFICE: closure. CEO: approvals only. PAINTER: create bodywork extras only. SERVICE_ADVISOR: read-only.

## Extras
- PAINTER creates bodywork_extras with description + image in bucket `extras-images`. Default status IN_TREATMENT.
- Only SERVICE_MANAGER may update extra status (IN_TREATMENT | REJECTED | DONE).

## Code
- Use `src/lib/supabase/client.ts` in client components, `src/lib/supabase/server.ts` in Server Components/Route Handlers.
- Types from `src/types/database.ts`. Prefer typed Supabase client with `Database` type.
- Keep UI and API modular; no business UI in foundation—only infrastructure and schema.
